Note: Runa Serverless Computing Abstractions Module
Note: Provides universal serverless computing patterns and deployment abstractions
Note: Following Runa specification patterns with natural language syntax

Note: Built-in functions are automatically available in Runa programs
Note: No imports required for built-ins like create_runtime_error, execute_command, etc.

Note: Generic Serverless Function type definition
Type ServerlessFunction is Dictionary with:
    function_name as String,
    runtime as String,
    handler as String,
    memory_size_mb as Integer,
    timeout_seconds as Integer,
    environment_variables as Dictionary[String, String],
    trigger_type as String,
    trigger_config as Dictionary[String, Any],
    code_location as String,
    deployment_package as Optional[String],
    provisioned_concurrency as Optional[Integer],
    reserved_concurrency as Optional[Integer],
    layers as List[String],
    vpc_config as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    dead_letter_config as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    tracing_config as Dictionary[String, String],
    tags as Dictionary[String, String],
    status as String,
    last_modified as Integer,
    version as String,
    description as String

Note: Serverless API Gateway type definition
Type ServerlessAPI is Dictionary with:
    api_id as String,
    api_name as String,
    api_type as String,
    protocol_type as String,
    routes as List[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    stages as List[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    cors_configuration as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    throttle_config as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    authorizers as List[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    domain_name as Optional[String],
    certificate_arn as Optional[String],
    endpoint_url as String,
    created_date as Integer,
    api_key_selection_expression as Optional[String],
    description as String,
    tags as Dictionary[String, String]

Note: Serverless Event Source type definition
Type ServerlessEventSource is Dictionary with:
    source_id as String,
    source_type as String,
    source_arn as String,
    function_name as String,
    batch_size as Optional[Integer],
    maximum_batching_window as Optional[Integer],
    starting_position as Optional[String],
    parallelization_factor as Optional[Integer],
    maximum_record_age as Optional[Integer],
    bisect_batch_on_function_error as Optional[Boolean],
    maximum_retry_attempts as Optional[Integer],
    destination_config as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    source_access_configurations as List[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    tumbling_window_in_seconds as Optional[Integer],
    state as String,
    state_transition_reason as String,
    last_modified as Integer,
    last_processing_result as String

Note: Serverless Deployment type definition
Type ServerlessDeployment is Dictionary with:
    deployment_id as String,
    application_name as String,
    stage as String,
    region as String,
    provider as String,
    functions as List[ServerlessFunction],
    api_gateways as List[ServerlessAPI],
    event_sources as List[ServerlessEventSource],
    resources as List[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    outputs as Dictionary[String, Any],
    stack_name as String,
    deployment_bucket as Optional[String],
    compilation_artifacts as List[String],
    package_individually as Boolean,
    exclude_dev_dependencies as Boolean,
    deployment_status as String,
    created_at as Integer,
    deployed_at as Optional[Integer],
    last_updated as Optional[Integer]

Note: Serverless Framework Configuration type definition
Type ServerlessConfig is Dictionary with:
    service_name as String,
    framework_version as String,
    provider_config as Dictionary[String, Any],
    functions_config as Dictionary[String, Any],
    resources_config as Dictionary[String, Any],
    plugins as List[String],
    custom_config as Dictionary[String, Any],
    package_config as Dictionary[String, Any],
    layers_config as Dictionary[String, Any],
    step_functions as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    config_validation_policy as String,
    deprecation_notification_mode as String

Note: Universal serverless function deployment
Process called "deploy_serverless_function" that takes function_config as ServerlessFunction and provider as String and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns ServerlessFunction:
    Match provider:
        When "aws":
            Return deploy_aws_lambda with function_config as function_config and options as options
        When "azure":
            Return deploy_azure_function with function_config as function_config and options as options
        When "gcp":
            Return deploy_gcp_function with function_config as function_config and options as options
        When "netlify":
            Return deploy_netlify_function with function_config as function_config and options as options
        When "vercel":
            Return deploy_vercel_function with function_config as function_config and options as options
        Otherwise:
            Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "deploy_serverless_function" and context as dictionary with:
                "provider" as provider,
                "error" as "Unsupported serverless provider"

Note: Deploy AWS Lambda function using serverless patterns
Process called "deploy_aws_lambda" that takes function_config as ServerlessFunction and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns ServerlessFunction:
    Let parameters be list containing
    Add "--function-name" to parameters
    Add function_config["function_name"] to parameters
    Add "--runtime" to parameters
    Add function_config["runtime"] to parameters
    Add "--role" to parameters
    Add options["role_arn"] to parameters
    Add "--handler" to parameters
    Add function_config["handler"] to parameters
    Add "--zip-file" to parameters
    Add "fileb://" with message function_config["deployment_package"] to parameters
    Add "--memory-size" to parameters
    Add function_config["memory_size_mb"] to parameters
    Add "--timeout" to parameters
    Add function_config["timeout_seconds"] to parameters
    Add "--output" to parameters
    Add "json" to parameters
    
    Note: Add environment variables
    If length of function_config["environment_variables"] is greater than 0:
        Let env_vars_string be "Variables={"
        Let first be true
        For each key and value in function_config["environment_variables"]:
            If not first:
                Set env_vars_string to env_vars_string with message ","
            Set env_vars_string to env_vars_string with message key with message "=" with message value
            Set first to false
        Set env_vars_string to env_vars_string with message "}"
        Add "--environment" to parameters
        Add env_vars_string to parameters
    
    Note: Add VPC configuration
    If function_config["vpc_config"] is not null:
        Let vpc_config be function_config["vpc_config"]
        Let subnets_string be join_list with list as vpc_config["subnet_ids"] and separator as ","
        Let security_groups_string be join_list with list as vpc_config["security_group_ids"] and separator as ","
        Add "--vpc-config" to parameters
        Add "SubnetIds=" with message subnets_string with message ",SecurityGroupIds=" with message security_groups_string to parameters
    
    Note: Add layers
    If length of function_config["layers"] is greater than 0:
        Let layers_string be join_list with list as function_config["layers"] and separator as " "
        Add "--layers" to parameters
        Add layers_string to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_command with command as "aws lambda create-function " with message join_list with list as parameters and separator as " "
    
    If result["exit_code"] is not equal to 0:
        Note: Try updating if creation failed
        Let update_parameters be list containing
        Add "--function-name" to update_parameters
        Add function_config["function_name"] to update_parameters
        Add "--zip-file" to update_parameters
        Add "fileb://" with message function_config["deployment_package"] to update_parameters
        Add "--output" to update_parameters
        Add "json" to update_parameters
        
        Let update_result be execute_command with command as "aws lambda update-function-code " with message join_list with list as update_parameters and separator as " "
        If update_result["exit_code"] is not equal to 0:
            Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "deploy_aws_lambda" and context as dictionary with:
                "function_name" as function_config["function_name"],
                "create_error" as result["stderr"],
                "update_error" as update_result["stderr"]
    
    Note: Configure trigger if specified
    If function_config["trigger_type"] is not equal to "manual":
        Let trigger_result be configure_aws_lambda_trigger with function_name as function_config["function_name"] and trigger_type as function_config["trigger_type"] and trigger_config as function_config["trigger_config"]
        If not trigger_result:
            Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "deploy_aws_lambda" and context as dictionary with:
                "function_name" as function_config["function_name"],
                "error" as "Failed to configure trigger"
    
    Note: Update function metadata
    Set function_config["status"] to "DEPLOYED"
    Set function_config["last_modified"] to get_current_timestamp
    Set function_config["version"] to "$LATEST"
    
    Return function_config

Note: Configure AWS Lambda trigger
Process called "configure_aws_lambda_trigger" that takes function_name as String and trigger_type as String and trigger_config as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Boolean:
    Match trigger_type:
        When "api_gateway":
            Return configure_api_gateway_trigger with function_name as function_name and config as trigger_config
        When "s3":
            Return configure_s3_trigger with function_name as function_name and config as trigger_config
        When "dynamodb":
            Return configure_dynamodb_trigger with function_name as function_name and config as trigger_config
        When "kinesis":
            Return configure_kinesis_trigger with function_name as function_name and config as trigger_config
        When "sqs":
            Return configure_sqs_trigger with function_name as function_name and config as trigger_config
        When "cloudwatch":
            Return configure_cloudwatch_trigger with function_name as function_name and config as trigger_config
        Otherwise:
            Return true

Note: Configure API Gateway trigger for Lambda
Process called "configure_api_gateway_trigger" that takes function_name as String and config as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Boolean:
    Let permission_params be list containing
    Add "--function-name" to permission_params
    Add function_name to permission_params
    Add "--statement-id" to permission_params
    Add "api-gateway-invoke" to permission_params
    Add "--action" to permission_params
    Add "lambda:InvokeFunction" to permission_params
    Add "--principal" to permission_params
    Add "apigateway.amazonaws.com" to permission_params
    Add "--output" to permission_params
    Add "json" to permission_params
    
    Let result be execute_command with command as "aws lambda add-permission " with message join_list with list as permission_params and separator as " "
    Return result["exit_code"] is equal to 0

Note: Configure S3 trigger for Lambda
Process called "configure_s3_trigger" that takes function_name as String and config as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Boolean:
    Let notification_config be dictionary with:
        "LambdaConfigurations" as list containing dictionary with:
            "Id" as "lambda-trigger",
            "LambdaFunctionArn" as get_lambda_function_arn with function_name as function_name,
            "Events" as config["events"],
            "Filter" as (config["filter"] if config contains key "filter" otherwise dictionary containing)
    
    Let config_json be to_json with data as notification_config
    Let temp_file be "/tmp/s3-notification-config.json"
    Let write_result be write_file_content with file_path as temp_file and content as config_json
    
    If not write_result:
        Return false
    
    Let s3_params be list containing
    Add "--bucket" to s3_params
    Add config["bucket_name"] to s3_params
    Add "--notification-configuration" to s3_params
    Add "file://" with message temp_file to s3_params
    Add "--output" to s3_params
    Add "json" to s3_params
    
    Let result be execute_command with command as "aws s3api put-bucket-notification-configuration " with message join_list with list as s3_params and separator as " "
    Let cleanup_result be execute_command with command as "rm -f " with message temp_file
    
    Return result["exit_code"] is equal to 0

Note: Deploy Azure Function using serverless patterns
Process called "deploy_azure_function" that takes function_config as ServerlessFunction and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns ServerlessFunction:
    Let parameters be list containing
    Add "--name" to parameters
    Add function_config["function_name"] to parameters
    Add "--resource-group" to parameters
    Add options["resource_group"] to parameters
    Add "--storage-account" to parameters
    Add options["storage_account"] to parameters
    Add "--runtime" to parameters
    Add function_config["runtime"] to parameters
    Add "--consumption-plan-location" to parameters
    Add options["location"] to parameters
    Add "--output" to parameters
    Add "json" to parameters
    
    Note: Add runtime version if specified
    If options contains key "runtime_version":
        Add "--runtime-version" to parameters
        Add options["runtime_version"] to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_command with command as "az functionapp create " with message join_list with list as parameters and separator as " "
    
    If result["exit_code"] is not equal to 0:
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "deploy_azure_function" and context as dictionary with:
            "function_name" as function_config["function_name"],
            "error" as result["stderr"]
    
    Note: Deploy function code if provided
    If function_config["deployment_package"] is not null:
        Let deploy_result be deploy_azure_function_code with function_name as function_config["function_name"] and resource_group as options["resource_group"] and deployment_package as function_config["deployment_package"]
        If not deploy_result:
            Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "deploy_azure_function" and context as dictionary with:
                "function_name" as function_config["function_name"],
                "error" as "Failed to deploy function code"
    
    Note: Configure app settings (environment variables)
    If length of function_config["environment_variables"] is greater than 0:
        Let settings_result be configure_azure_function_settings with function_name as function_config["function_name"] and resource_group as options["resource_group"] and settings as function_config["environment_variables"]
        If not settings_result:
            Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "deploy_azure_function" and context as dictionary with:
                "function_name" as function_config["function_name"],
                "error" as "Failed to configure app settings"
    
    Note: Update function metadata
    Set function_config["status"] to "DEPLOYED"
    Set function_config["last_modified"] to get_current_timestamp
    Set function_config["version"] to "1"
    
    Return function_config

Note: Deploy function code to Azure
Process called "deploy_azure_function_code" that takes function_name as String and resource_group as String and deployment_package as String returns Boolean:
    Let parameters be list containing
    Add "--name" to parameters
    Add function_name to parameters
    Add "--resource-group" to parameters
    Add resource_group to parameters
    Add "--src" to parameters
    Add deployment_package to parameters
    Add "--output" to parameters
    Add "json" to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_command with command as "az functionapp deployment source config-zip " with message join_list with list as parameters and separator as " "
    Return result["exit_code"] is equal to 0

Note: Configure Azure Function app settings
Process called "configure_azure_function_settings" that takes function_name as String and resource_group as String and settings as Dictionary[String, String] returns Boolean:
    For each key and value in settings:
        Let setting_params be list containing
        Add "--name" to setting_params
        Add function_name to setting_params
        Add "--resource-group" to setting_params
        Add resource_group to setting_params
        Add "--settings" to setting_params
        Add key with message "=" with message value to setting_params
        Add "--output" to setting_params
        Add "json" to setting_params
        
        Let result be execute_command with command as "az functionapp config appsettings set " with message join_list with list as setting_params and separator as " "
        If result["exit_code"] is not equal to 0:
            Return false
    
    Return true

Note: Deploy GCP Cloud Function using serverless patterns
Process called "deploy_gcp_function" that takes function_config as ServerlessFunction and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns ServerlessFunction:
    Let parameters be list containing
    Add function_config["function_name"] to parameters
    Add "--region=" with message options["region"] to parameters
    Add "--runtime=" with message function_config["runtime"] to parameters
    Add "--source=" with message function_config["code_location"] to parameters
    Add "--format=json" to parameters
    
    Note: Configure trigger
    Match function_config["trigger_type"]:
        When "http":
            Add "--trigger-http" to parameters
        When "pubsub":
            If function_config["trigger_config"] contains key "topic":
                Add "--trigger-topic=" with message function_config["trigger_config"]["topic"] to parameters
        When "storage":
            If function_config["trigger_config"] contains key "bucket":
                Add "--trigger-bucket=" with message function_config["trigger_config"]["bucket"] to parameters
    
    Note: Add entry point
    Add "--entry-point=" with message function_config["handler"] to parameters
    
    Note: Add memory
    Add "--memory=" with message function_config["memory_size_mb"] with message "MB" to parameters
    
    Note: Add timeout
    Add "--timeout=" with message function_config["timeout_seconds"] with message "s" to parameters
    
    Note: Add environment variables
    If length of function_config["environment_variables"] is greater than 0:
        For each key and value in function_config["environment_variables"]:
            Add "--set-env-vars=" with message key with message "=" with message value to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_command with command as "gcloud functions deploy " with message join_list with list as parameters and separator as " "
    
    If result["exit_code"] is not equal to 0:
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "deploy_gcp_function" and context as dictionary with:
            "function_name" as function_config["function_name"],
            "error" as result["stderr"]
    
    Note: Update function metadata
    Set function_config["status"] to "DEPLOYED"
    Set function_config["last_modified"] to get_current_timestamp
    Set function_config["version"] to "1"
    
    Return function_config

Note: Deploy Netlify Function using serverless patterns
Process called "deploy_netlify_function" that takes function_config as ServerlessFunction and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns ServerlessFunction:
    Note: Netlify functions are deployed via git or CLI
    Let site_id be options["site_id"]
    
    Let parameters be list containing
    Add "--site=" with message site_id to parameters
    Add "--dir=" with message function_config["code_location"] to parameters
    Add "--functions=" with message options["functions_dir"] to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_command with command as "netlify deploy " with message join_list with list as parameters and separator as " "
    
    If result["exit_code"] is not equal to 0:
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "deploy_netlify_function" and context as dictionary with:
            "function_name" as function_config["function_name"],
            "error" as result["stderr"]
    
    Note: Update function metadata
    Set function_config["status"] to "DEPLOYED"
    Set function_config["last_modified"] to get_current_timestamp
    Set function_config["version"] to "1"
    
    Return function_config

Note: Deploy Vercel Function using serverless patterns
Process called "deploy_vercel_function" that takes function_config as ServerlessFunction and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns ServerlessFunction:
    Let parameters be list containing
    Add function_config["code_location"] to parameters
    Add "--prod" to parameters
    
    Note: Add environment variables
    If length of function_config["environment_variables"] is greater than 0:
        For each key and value in function_config["environment_variables"]:
            Add "--env" to parameters
            Add key with message "=" with message value to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_command with command as "vercel " with message join_list with list as parameters and separator as " "
    
    If result["exit_code"] is not equal to 0:
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "deploy_vercel_function" and context as dictionary with:
            "function_name" as function_config["function_name"],
            "error" as result["stderr"]
    
    Note: Update function metadata
    Set function_config["status"] to "DEPLOYED"
    Set function_config["last_modified"] to get_current_timestamp
    Set function_config["version"] to "1"
    
    Return function_config

Note: Create serverless API Gateway
Process called "create_serverless_api" that takes api_config as ServerlessAPI and provider as String and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns ServerlessAPI:
    Match provider:
        When "aws":
            Return create_aws_api_gateway with api_config as api_config and options as options
        When "azure":
            Return create_azure_api_management with api_config as api_config and options as options
        When "gcp":
            Return create_gcp_api_gateway with api_config as api_config and options as options
        Otherwise:
            Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "create_serverless_api" and context as dictionary with:
                "provider" as provider,
                "error" as "Unsupported API provider"

Note: Create AWS API Gateway
Process called "create_aws_api_gateway" that takes api_config as ServerlessAPI and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns ServerlessAPI:
    Let parameters be list containing
    Add "--name" to parameters
    Add api_config["api_name"] to parameters
    Add "--protocol-type" to parameters
    Add api_config["protocol_type"] to parameters
    Add "--output" to parameters
    Add "json" to parameters
    
    Note: Add CORS configuration
    If api_config["cors_configuration"] is not null:
        Let cors_config be api_config["cors_configuration"]
        Add "--cors-configuration" to parameters
        Add "AllowCredentials=" with message cors_config["allow_credentials"] with message ",AllowHeaders=" with message join_list with list as cors_config["allow_headers"] and separator as "," with message ",AllowMethods=" with message join_list with list as cors_config["allow_methods"] and separator as "," with message ",AllowOrigins=" with message join_list with list as cors_config["allow_origins"] and separator as "," to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_command with command as "aws apigatewayv2 create-api " with message join_list with list as parameters and separator as " "
    
    If result["exit_code"] is not equal to 0:
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "create_aws_api_gateway" and context as dictionary with:
            "api_name" as api_config["api_name"],
            "error" as result["stderr"]
    
    Let api_data be parse_json with json_string as result["stdout"]
    
    Note: Update API configuration with created data
    Set api_config["api_id"] to api_data["ApiId"]
    Set api_config["endpoint_url"] to api_data["ApiEndpoint"]
    Set api_config["created_date"] to parse_api_timestamp with timestamp as api_data["CreatedDate"]
    
    Note: Create routes if specified
    If length of api_config["routes"] is greater than 0:
        For each route in api_config["routes"]:
            Let route_result be create_api_gateway_route with api_id as api_config["api_id"] and route_config as route
            If not route_result:
                Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "create_aws_api_gateway" and context as dictionary with:
                    "api_id" as api_config["api_id"],
                    "error" as "Failed to create route"
    
    Return api_config

Note: Create API Gateway route
Process called "create_api_gateway_route" that takes api_id as String and route_config as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Boolean:
    Let parameters be list containing
    Add "--api-id" to parameters
    Add api_id to parameters
    Add "--route-key" to parameters
    Add route_config["method"] with message " " with message route_config["path"] to parameters
    Add "--target" to parameters
    Add "integrations/" with message route_config["integration_id"] to parameters
    Add "--output" to parameters
    Add "json" to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_command with command as "aws apigatewayv2 create-route " with message join_list with list as parameters and separator as " "
    Return result["exit_code"] is equal to 0

Note: Deploy serverless application from configuration
Process called "deploy_serverless_application" that takes config_file as String and stage as String and provider as String and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns ServerlessDeployment:
    Let deployment be dictionary with:
        "deployment_id" as generate_deployment_id,
        "application_name" as "unknown",
        "stage" as stage,
        "region" as (options["region"] if options contains key "region" otherwise "us-east-1"),
        "provider" as provider,
        "functions" as list containing,
        "api_gateways" as list containing,
        "event_sources" as list containing,
        "resources" as list containing,
        "outputs" as dictionary containing,
        "stack_name" as "unknown",
        "deployment_bucket" as (options["deployment_bucket"] if options contains key "deployment_bucket" otherwise null),
        "compilation_artifacts" as list containing,
        "package_individually" as false,
        "exclude_dev_dependencies" as true,
        "deployment_status" as "DEPLOYING",
        "created_at" as get_current_timestamp,
        "deployed_at" as null,
        "last_updated" as null
    
    Note: Parse configuration file
    Let config_data be parse_serverless_config with config_file as config_file
    Set deployment["application_name"] to config_data["service_name"]
    Set deployment["stack_name"] to config_data["service_name"] with message "-" with message stage
    
    Note: Deploy based on framework
    Match provider:
        When "serverless":
            Return deploy_with_serverless_framework with config_file as config_file and stage as stage and deployment as deployment and options as options
        When "sam":
            Return deploy_with_sam with config_file as config_file and stage as stage and deployment as deployment and options as options
        When "terraform":
            Return deploy_with_terraform with config_file as config_file and stage as stage and deployment as deployment and options as options
        Otherwise:
            Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "deploy_serverless_application" and context as dictionary with:
                "provider" as provider,
                "error" as "Unsupported deployment framework"

Note: Deploy with Serverless Framework
Process called "deploy_with_serverless_framework" that takes config_file as String and stage as String and deployment as ServerlessDeployment and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns ServerlessDeployment:
    Let parameters be list containing
    Add "deploy" to parameters
    Add "--stage" to parameters
    Add stage to parameters
    Add "--config" to parameters
    Add config_file to parameters
    Add "--verbose" to parameters
    
    Note: Add region if specified
    If options contains key "region":
        Add "--region" to parameters
        Add options["region"] to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_command with command as "serverless " with message join_list with list as parameters and separator as " "
    
    If result["exit_code"] is not equal to 0:
        Set deployment["deployment_status"] to "FAILED"
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "deploy_with_serverless_framework" and context as dictionary with:
            "config_file" as config_file,
            "stage" as stage,
            "error" as result["stderr"]
    
    Note: Parse deployment outputs
    Let outputs be parse_serverless_outputs with output as result["stdout"]
    Set deployment["outputs"] to outputs
    Set deployment["deployment_status"] to "DEPLOYED"
    Set deployment["deployed_at"] to get_current_timestamp
    
    Return deployment

Note: Deploy with AWS SAM
Process called "deploy_with_sam" that takes config_file as String and stage as String and deployment as ServerlessDeployment and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns ServerlessDeployment:
    Note: Build the application first
    Let build_params be list containing
    Add "build" to build_params
    Add "--template" to build_params
    Add config_file to build_params
    
    Let build_result be execute_command with command as "sam " with message join_list with list as build_params and separator as " "
    
    If build_result["exit_code"] is not equal to 0:
        Set deployment["deployment_status"] to "FAILED"
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "deploy_with_sam" and context as dictionary with:
            "config_file" as config_file,
            "error" as build_result["stderr"]
    
    Note: Deploy the application
    Let deploy_params be list containing
    Add "deploy" to deploy_params
    Add "--stack-name" to deploy_params
    Add deployment["stack_name"] to deploy_params
    Add "--capabilities" to deploy_params
    Add "CAPABILITY_IAM" to deploy_params
    Add "--no-confirm-changeset" to deploy_params
    
    Note: Add S3 bucket for deployment artifacts
    If deployment["deployment_bucket"] is not null:
        Add "--s3-bucket" to deploy_params
        Add deployment["deployment_bucket"] to deploy_params
    
    Let deploy_result be execute_command with command as "sam " with message join_list with list as deploy_params and separator as " "
    
    If deploy_result["exit_code"] is not equal to 0:
        Set deployment["deployment_status"] to "FAILED"
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "deploy_with_sam" and context as dictionary with:
            "stack_name" as deployment["stack_name"],
            "error" as deploy_result["stderr"]
    
    Set deployment["deployment_status"] to "DEPLOYED"
    Set deployment["deployed_at"] to get_current_timestamp
    
    Return deployment

Note: Remove serverless application
Process called "remove_serverless_application" that takes deployment as ServerlessDeployment and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Boolean:
    Match deployment["provider"]:
        When "serverless":
            Return remove_with_serverless_framework with deployment as deployment and options as options
        When "sam":
            Return remove_with_sam with deployment as deployment and options as options
        When "terraform":
            Return remove_with_terraform with deployment as deployment and options as options
        Otherwise:
            Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "remove_serverless_application" and context as dictionary with:
                "provider" as deployment["provider"],
                "error" as "Unsupported removal framework"

Note: Remove with Serverless Framework
Process called "remove_with_serverless_framework" that takes deployment as ServerlessDeployment and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Boolean:
    Let parameters be list containing
    Add "remove" to parameters
    Add "--stage" to parameters
    Add deployment["stage"] to parameters
    Add "--verbose" to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_command with command as "serverless " with message join_list with list as parameters and separator as " "
    Return result["exit_code"] is equal to 0

Note: Monitor serverless function metrics
Process called "monitor_serverless_function" that takes function_name as String and provider as String and time_range as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Match provider:
        When "aws":
            Return get_aws_lambda_metrics with function_name as function_name and time_range as time_range
        When "azure":
            Return get_azure_function_metrics with function_name as function_name and time_range as time_range
        When "gcp":
            Return get_gcp_function_metrics with function_name as function_name and time_range as time_range
        Otherwise:
            Return dictionary with:
                "error" as "Unsupported monitoring provider",
                "metrics" as dictionary containing

Note: Get AWS Lambda metrics
Process called "get_aws_lambda_metrics" that takes function_name as String and time_range as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let end_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let start_time be end_time minus parse_time_range with time_range as time_range
    
    Let metrics be dictionary with:
        "invocations" as get_cloudwatch_metric with namespace as "AWS/Lambda" and metric_name as "Invocations" and function_name as function_name and start_time as start_time and end_time as end_time,
        "duration" as get_cloudwatch_metric with namespace as "AWS/Lambda" and metric_name as "Duration" and function_name as function_name and start_time as start_time and end_time as end_time,
        "errors" as get_cloudwatch_metric with namespace as "AWS/Lambda" and metric_name as "Errors" and function_name as function_name and start_time as start_time and end_time as end_time,
        "throttles" as get_cloudwatch_metric with namespace as "AWS/Lambda" and metric_name as "Throttles" and function_name as function_name and start_time as start_time and end_time as end_time,
        "concurrent_executions" as get_cloudwatch_metric with namespace as "AWS/Lambda" and metric_name as "ConcurrentExecutions" and function_name as function_name and start_time as start_time and end_time as end_time
    
    Return dictionary with:
        "function_name" as function_name,
        "provider" as "aws",
        "time_range" as time_range,
        "metrics" as metrics,
        "collected_at" as get_current_timestamp

Note: Scale serverless function
Process called "scale_serverless_function" that takes function_name as String and provider as String and scaling_config as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Boolean:
    Match provider:
        When "aws":
            Return scale_aws_lambda with function_name as function_name and scaling_config as scaling_config
        When "azure":
            Return scale_azure_function with function_name as function_name and scaling_config as scaling_config
        When "gcp":
            Return scale_gcp_function with function_name as function_name and scaling_config as scaling_config
        Otherwise:
            Return false

Note: Scale AWS Lambda function
Process called "scale_aws_lambda" that takes function_name as String and scaling_config as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Boolean:
    Note: Configure reserved concurrency
    If scaling_config contains key "reserved_concurrency":
        Let concurrency_params be list containing
        Add "--function-name" to concurrency_params
        Add function_name to concurrency_params
        Add "--reserved-concurrent-executions" to concurrency_params
        Add scaling_config["reserved_concurrency"] to concurrency_params
        Add "--output" to concurrency_params
        Add "json" to concurrency_params
        
        Let result be execute_command with command as "aws lambda put-reserved-concurrency-configuration " with message join_list with list as concurrency_params and separator as " "
        If result["exit_code"] is not equal to 0:
            Return false
    
    Note: Configure provisioned concurrency
    If scaling_config contains key "provisioned_concurrency":
        Let provisioned_params be list containing
        Add "--function-name" to provisioned_params
        Add function_name to provisioned_params
        Add "--qualifier" to provisioned_params
        Add "$LATEST" to provisioned_params
        Add "--provisioned-concurrency-config" to provisioned_params
        Add "ProvisionedConcurrencyUnits=" with message scaling_config["provisioned_concurrency"] to provisioned_params
        Add "--output" to provisioned_params
        Add "json" to provisioned_params
        
        Let provisioned_result be execute_command with command as "aws lambda put-provisioned-concurrency-config " with message join_list with list as provisioned_params and separator as " "
        If provisioned_result["exit_code"] is not equal to 0:
            Return false
    
    Return true

Note: Helper function to generate deployment ID
Process called "generate_deployment_id" returns String:
    Let timestamp be get_current_timestamp
    Return "deploy-" with message timestamp

Note: Helper function to parse time range
Process called "parse_time_range" that takes time_range as String returns Integer:
    Match time_range:
        When "1h":
            Return 3600
        When "6h":
            Return 21600
        When "24h":
            Return 86400
        When "7d":
            Return 604800
        When "30d":
            Return 2592000
        Otherwise:
            Return 3600

Note: Helper function to join list with separator
Process called "join_list" that takes list as List[String] and separator as String returns String:
    If length of list is equal to 0:
        Return ""
    
    Let result be list[0]
    For index from 1 to (length of list minus 1):
        Set result to result with message separator with message list[index]
    
    Return result

Note: Helper function to get Lambda function ARN
Process called "get_lambda_function_arn" that takes function_name as String returns String:
    Let params be list containing
    Add "--function-name" to params
    Add function_name to params
    Add "--output" to params
    Add "json" to params
    
    Let result be execute_command with command as "aws lambda get-function " with message join_list with list as params and separator as " "
    If result["exit_code"] is equal to 0:
        Let function_data be parse_json with json_string as result["stdout"]
        If function_data contains key "Configuration" and function_data["Configuration"] contains key "FunctionArn":
            Return function_data["Configuration"]["FunctionArn"]
    
    Return ""

Note: Helper function to parse serverless configuration
Process called "parse_serverless_config" that takes config_file as String returns ServerlessConfig:
    Note: Parse serverless framework configuration from YAML/JSON file
    Try:
        Let file_content be system_call_read_file_content with path as config_file
        
        Note: Detect file format by extension
        Let config_data be None
        If config_file contains ".yml" or config_file contains ".yaml":
            Set config_data to system_call_parse_yaml with yaml_string as file_content
        Otherwise:
            Set config_data to system_call_parse_json with json_string as file_content
        
        Return dictionary with:
            "service_name" as (config_data["service"] if config_data contains key "service" otherwise "unknown-service"),
            "framework_version" as (config_data["frameworkVersion"] if config_data contains key "frameworkVersion" otherwise "3.0.0"),
            "provider_config" as (config_data["provider"] if config_data contains key "provider" otherwise dictionary containing),
            "functions_config" as (config_data["functions"] if config_data contains key "functions" otherwise dictionary containing),
            "resources_config" as (config_data["resources"] if config_data contains key "resources" otherwise dictionary containing),
            "plugins" as (config_data["plugins"] if config_data contains key "plugins" otherwise list containing),
            "custom_config" as (config_data["custom"] if config_data contains key "custom" otherwise dictionary containing),
            "package_config" as (config_data["package"] if config_data contains key "package" otherwise dictionary containing),
            "layers_config" as (config_data["layers"] if config_data contains key "layers" otherwise dictionary containing),
            "step_functions" as (config_data["stepFunctions"] if config_data contains key "stepFunctions" otherwise None),
            "config_validation_policy" as (config_data["configValidationMode"] if config_data contains key "configValidationMode" otherwise "warn"),
            "deprecation_notification_mode" as (config_data["deprecationNotificationMode"] if config_data contains key "deprecationNotificationMode" otherwise "warn")
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Return default configuration if parsing fails
        Return dictionary with:
            "service_name" as "unknown-service",
            "framework_version" as "3.0.0",
            "provider_config" as dictionary containing,
            "functions_config" as dictionary containing,
            "resources_config" as dictionary containing,
            "plugins" as list containing,
            "custom_config" as dictionary containing,
            "package_config" as dictionary containing,
            "layers_config" as dictionary containing,
            "step_functions" as None,
            "config_validation_policy" as "warn",
            "deprecation_notification_mode" as "warn"

Note: Helper function to parse serverless outputs
Process called "parse_serverless_outputs" that takes output as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Parse deployment outputs from serverless framework deployment
    Try:
        Let parsed_output be system_call_parse_json with json_string as output
        Return parsed_output
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Return empty dictionary if output parsing fails
        Return dictionary containing

Note: Helper function to get CloudWatch metric
Process called "get_cloudwatch_metric" that takes namespace as String and metric_name as String and function_name as String and start_time as Integer and end_time as Integer returns List[Dictionary[String, Any]]:
    Note: Query CloudWatch metrics for serverless function monitoring
    Try:
        Let metrics_result be system_call_query_cloudwatch_metrics with:
            namespace as namespace
            metric_name as metric_name
            dimensions as dictionary containing "FunctionName" as function_name
            start_time as start_time
            end_time as end_time
        
        Return metrics_result.datapoints
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Return empty list if CloudWatch query fails
        Return list containing

Note: Helper function to parse API timestamp
Process called "parse_api_timestamp" that takes timestamp as String returns Integer:
    Note: Parse ISO 8601 timestamps used in serverless APIs to Unix timestamp
    Try:
        Let parsed_timestamp be system_call_parse_iso8601_timestamp with timestamp as timestamp
        Return parsed_timestamp
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Fallback to current timestamp if parsing fails
        Return system_call_get_current_time_seconds as Integer

Note: Helper function to get current timestamp
Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Integer:
    Let result be execute_command with command as "date +%s"
    Return to_integer with value as trim with text as result["stdout"]

Note: Helper function to write file content
Process called "write_file_content" that takes file_path as String and content as String returns Boolean:
    Let command be "echo '" with message content with message "' > " with message file_path
    Let result be execute_command with command as command
    Return result["exit_code"] is equal to 0

Note: Helper function to convert data to JSON
Process called "to_json" that takes data as Dictionary[String, Any] returns String:
    Note: Convert dictionary to JSON string using system JSON serializer
    Try:
        Let json_string be system_call_serialize_to_json with data as data
        Return json_string
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Return empty JSON object if serialization fails
        Return "{}"

Note: Helper function to parse JSON
Process called "parse_json" that takes json_string as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Parse JSON string using system JSON parser with error handling
    Try:
        Let parsed_data be system_call_parse_json with json_string as json_string
        Return parsed_data
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Return empty dictionary if JSON parsing fails
        Return dictionary containing